    "code": "012", 
    "data": "If you wish to offer a prayer and need to go to toilet, you may begin with the latter. There are many reported etiquettes of going to toilet. However, I will hereinafter mention some of them briefly:\nYou may precede your left foot to the right when entering the water closet (or the place where you excrete) and say the following:\nبِسْمِ اللهِ وَبِاللهِ\nBISMILLAAHE WA BILLAAHE\nIn the Name of Allah (I begin) and in Allah (I trust).\nاَعُوذُ بِاللهِ مِنَ الرِّجْسِ النَّجِسِ\nA-O’OZO BILLAAHE MENAR RIJSIN NAJESIL\nI pray Allah’s protection against the filthy, the impure,\nالْخَبِيْثِ الْمُخْبِثِ\nKHABEESIL MUKHBESISH\nthe wicked, and the source of wickedness;\nالشَّيْطَانِ الرَّجِيْمِ\nSHAYTAANIR RAJEEME.\nnamely, Satan the accursed.\nWhen you try to take off, you may utter the basmalah:\nبِسْمِ اللهِ الرَّحْمٰنِ الرَّحِيْمِ\nBISMIL LAAHIR RAHMAANIR  RAHEEME\nIn the Name of Allah; the All-beneficent, the All-merciful.\n At such a situation, and all similar situations, you must try to cover your private parts, letting nobody see them. It is haram (i.e. religiously unlawful) to sit, for excretion, facing the kiblah direction or giving it one’s back.\nWhile excreting, it is recommended to say the following:\nاَللّٰهُمَّ اَطْعِمْنِي طَيِّبًا فِيْ عَافِيَةٍ\nALLAAHUMMA AT-I’MNEE TAYYEBAN FEE A’AFEYATIN\nO Allah, (please) nourish me pleasant food in wellbeing\nوَ اَخْرِجْهُ مِنِّيْ خَبِيْثًا فِيْ عَافِيَةٍ\nWA AKHRIJHO MINNEE KHABEESAN FEE A’AFEYATIN\nand make me excrete it repulsive in wellbeing.\nIf your sight falls on the excrement, you may say the following:\nاَللّٰهُمَّ ارْزُقْنِي الْحَلَالَ\nALLAAHUMMAR ZUQNIL HALAALA\nO Allah, (please) provide me with the legally gotten (sustenance)\nوَ جَنِّبْنِيْ الْحَرَامَ\nWA JANNIBNIL HARAAMA\nand keep me away from the illegally gotten.\nWhen you finish and want to clean yourself, you may first of all try to make sure that you have discharged the entire waste. Then, you may say the supplicatory prayer that is said when one’s eye falls on water:\nاَلْحَمْدُ لِلهِ الَّذِيْ جَعَلَ الْمَاءَ طَهُوْرًا\nALHAMDO LILLAAHIL LAZEE JA-A’LAL MAA-A TAHOORAN\nAll praise be to Allah Who has made water pure\nوَ لَمْ يَجْعَلْهُ نَجِسًا\nWA LAM YAJ-A’LHO NAJESAN\nbut has not made it impure.\nWhile cleaning yourself from the waste, you may say the following:\nاَللّٰهُمَّ حَصِّنْ فَرْجِيْ وَ اَعِفَّهٗ\nALLAAHUMMA HASSIN FARJEE WA A-I’FFAHU\nO Allah, make me guard my chastity, chasten me,\nوَ اسْتُرْ عَوْرَتِيْ\nWAS TUR A’WRATEE\ncover my private parts,\nوَ حَرِّمْنِيْ عَلَى النَّارِ\nWA HARRIMNEE A’LAN NAARE.\nand forbid Hellfire from consuming me.\nWhen you finish and stand up, you may rub your abdomen with your right hand and say the following:\nاَلْحَمْدُ لِلهِ الَّذِيْ اَمَاطَ عَنِّيَ الْاَذٰى\nALHAMDO LILLAAHIL LAZEE AMAATA A’NNEYAL AZAA\nAll praise be to Allah Who has warded off harm from me,\nوَ هَنَّاَنِيْ طَعَامِيْ وَ شَرَابِيْ\nWA HANNAANEE TA-A’AMEE WA SHARAABEE\nmade me find the pleasure of my food and drink,\nوَ عَافَانِيْ مِنَ الْبَلْوٰى\nWA A’AFAANEE MENAL BALWAA\nand freed me from plague.\nYou may then leave the water closet (or the place where you have excreted), preceding your right foot to the left and saying the following:\nاَلْحَمْدُ لِلهِ الَّذِيْ عَرَّفَنِيْ لَذَّتَهٗ\nALHAMDO LILLAAHIL LAZEE A’RRAFANEE LAZZATAHU\nAll praise be to Allah Who has made me find its pleasure,\nوَ اَبْقٰى فِي جَسَدِيْ قُوَّتَهٗ\nWA ABQAA FEE JASADEE QUWWATAHU\nkept in my body its power,\nوَ اَخْرَجَ عَنِّيْ اَذَاهٗ\nWA AKHRAJA A’NNEE AZAAHU\nand discharged its harm from me.\nيَا لَهَا نِعْمَةً\nYAA LAHAA NE’MATAN\nHow a pleasant bliss it is!\nيَا لَهَا نِعْمَةً\nYAA LAHAA NE’MATAN\nHow a pleasant bliss it is!\nيَا لَهَا نِعْمَةً\nYAA LAHAA NE’MATAN\nHow a pleasant bliss it is!\nلَا يُقَدِّرُ الْقَادِرُوْنَ قَدْرَهَا\nLAA YOQADDERUL QAADEROONA QADRAHAA\nNo estimators can assign its value.", 
    "title": "Etiquettes of Going to Toilet"
}